    => Mode aka Average
    Highest frequency in the frequency table
    It's possible for it to be no mode. e.g. when all scores have the same
    frequency. Or if there is no 1 score that is most frequent.

    => Median
    the *value in the middle* when the data is ordered.  Not affected by
    extreme values.  If the overall frequency is even then we need to take
    the average of the 2 numbers in the middle.

    So the index is overall frequency + 1

    and the median is data-set[overall frequency + 1]'

    `Formula = (n+1) / 2`


